# read ASV table

str(taxa)
## 'data.frame':    162 obs. of  2 variables:
##  $ Taxon     : Factor w/ 106 levels "Bacteria","Bacteria_Acidobacteria_Blastocatellia (Subgroup 4)_Pyrinomonadales_Pyrinomonadaceae_RB41",..: 79 79 79 79 79 79 79 50 80 50 ...
##  $ Confidence: num  0.998 0.998 0.998 0.998 0.998 ...
# combine otu table and taxa info
com <- transform(merge(taxa, com, by="row.names"), row.names=Row.names, Row.names=NULL)
com <- com[, -2]

## [1] 162  24
warning("double check is the table rarified or not?")
range(colSums(com[, -1]))
## [1] 1400 1400
(rarefactiondepth <- mean(colSums(com[, -1])))
## [1] 1400

Prepare dataframe for plotting

# combine ASVs have same taxonomy
df <- aggregate(com[,-1], list(com$Taxon), sum)
row.names(df) <- df$Group.1
df <- df[, -1]
df <- 100*df/rarefactiondepth
df <- t(df)
df <- as.data.frame(df)
dim(df)
## [1]  23 106
# split treatment info
group_info <- data.frame(row.names=rownames(df), t(as.data.frame(strsplit(rownames(df),"_"))))
head(group_info)
##                           X1      X2           X3 X4
## L3_Control_heterozygous_1 L3 Control heterozygous  1
## L3_Control_heterozygous_2 L3 Control heterozygous  2
## L3_Control_heterozygous_3 L3 Control heterozygous  3
## L3_Control_heterozygous_4 L3 Control heterozygous  4
## L3_Control_heterozygous_5 L3 Control heterozygous  5
## L3_Control_heterozygous_6 L3 Control heterozygous  6
df <- data.frame(Treatments = as.factor(group_info[,2]), 
                 replicates = as.factor(group_info[,4]),
                 df)
df$Treatments <- as.character(df$Treatments)
df$Treatments[df$Treatments == "VitaminB5"] <- "Pantothenate"
df$Treatments <- factor(df$Treatments)
df$Treatments[df$Treatments == "VitaminB5"] <- "Pantothenate"
levels(df$Treatments)
## [1] "Control"      "Pantethine"   "Pantothenate"
df <- melt(df, id.vars = c("Treatments", "replicates"))
head(df)
##   Treatments replicates variable     value
## 1    Control          1 Bacteria 0.0000000
## 2    Control          2 Bacteria 0.2142857
## 3    Control          3 Bacteria 0.0000000
## 4    Control          4 Bacteria 0.0000000
## 5    Control          5 Bacteria 0.0000000
## 6    Control          6 Bacteria 0.4285714
# log transform relative abundance
df$logvalue <- log10(df$value)

Heatmap

(p <- ggplot(df, aes(replicates, variable, fill = logvalue)) + 
    geom_tile(colour = "white") + 
    scale_fill_distiller(palette = "RdYlBu") +
    facet_grid(. ~ Treatments, scales = "free_x", space = "free_x") +
    labs(x = "Replicates", y = "", title = "L3 stage",
         fill = "Relative \nabundance (%)") + 
    scale_x_discrete(expand = c(0, 0)) +
    scale_y_discrete(expand = c(0, 0)) + 
    theme_bw() +
    theme(text = element_text(size=11),
          axis.ticks = element_blank(),
          strip.background = element_blank(),
          strip.text=element_text(face = "bold", size = 11),
          legend.box.background = element_rect(),
          legend.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
          panel.grid.major = element_blank(), 
          panel.grid.minor = element_blank()) )
